      "content": "I guess I'm just seeing a lot of people argue that the whole thing was a massive blunder because the cost in stability was so high. If the end result is just more chaos and failed states, does the \"short term\" achievement even matter in the real world of geopolitics? It feels like we're prioritizing moralizing over actual strategic foresight.",
